(3, 7, 'HTML5', '<p><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">﻿</span>HTML 5 is the fifth and current version of HTML. It has improved the markup available for documents and has introduced application programming interfaces (API) and Document Object Model (DOM).&nbsp;<p></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(46, 71, 93); font-family: \" lexend=\"\" deca\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;\"=\"\">HTML5 introduced the placeholder attribute.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(46, 71, 93); font-family: \" lexend=\"\" deca\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" initial;=\"\" text-align:=\"\" var(--bs-body-text-align);\"=\"\">HTML5 supports one-way server-sent events. That means, data is continuously sent from a server to the browser.</span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(46, 71, 93); font-family: \" lexend=\"\" deca\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-size:=\"\" 18px;\"=\"\">HTML5 is supported by all the major browsers, including Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Opera, as well as iOS for Chrome and Safari and Android browsers. It can even work with the older and less popular browsers like Internet Explorer. That means when building with HTML5, you know that users will have a consistent experience on your site, no matter what browser they use or whether they’re on mobile or desktop.</span></p></p>', 'courses-3.jpg', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; color: rgb(33, 37, 41); font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, &quot;Liberation Sans&quot;, Arial, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">﻿</span><span style=\"font-size: 12px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: &quot;Open Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-weight: 600; text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">H