(9, 8, 'Android', '<p>﻿﻿<span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">﻿</span><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: initial; text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">Android OS is a Linux-based mobile operating system that primarily runs on smartphones and tablets.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-weight: initial; text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\">The Android platform includes an operating system&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-weight: initial; text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\">based upon the Linux kernel, a&nbsp;GUI, a web browser and end-user applications that can be downloaded.</span><p></p><p><span style=\"font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">﻿</span><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: initial; text-align: var(--bs-body-text-align);\">Android was released under the&nbsp;Apache&nbsp;v2 open source license; this allows for many variations of the OS to be developed for other devices, such as gaming consoles and digital cameras. Android is based on open source software, but most Android devices come preinstalled with a suite of proprietary software, such as Google Maps, YouTube, Google Chrome and Gmail.</span></p></p>', 'courses-3.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">﻿</span>﻿﻿<span style=\"font-size: 12px; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8); color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: \" open=\"\" sans\",=\"\" sans-serif;=\"\" font-weight:=\"\" 600;=\"\" text-align:=\"\" var(--bs-body-text-align);\"=\"\">Introduction to Android</span><p></p><ul style=\"font-size: 12px; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 2.6rem; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(85, 85, 85); font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; background-color: rg